      "It might be cool to compliment this with a `string.ngram(<min_gram>, <max_gram>)` which could basically just be a rewrite to:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.range(<min_gram>, <max_gram>).map(function (i) {\r\n  return string.split('').limit(i);\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.expr('foobar').ngram(1, 3) // -> [ 'f', 'fo', 'foo' ]\r\ntable.indexCreate('autocomplete', r.row('term').ngram(2, 5), { multi: true })\r\n```\r\n\r\nHaving some basic tokenizers like this as part of the ReQL API would make it more obvious that multi-indices can be used to solve use-cases like autocomplete and basic text-search."
